time required: 30 minutes
---

olive oil
2 unit onion
1 unit courgette
2 tbs balsamic vinegar
1 tbs water
1 tbs brown sugar
2 unit pizza bases
1 sachet pizza sauce
½ sachet dried oregano
1 packet goat cheese
1 bag salad leaves

Preheat the oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced (remove two wire racks first). Thinly slice the red onion. Peel the courgette into thin ribbons using a vegetable peeler. In a medium bowl, toss the courgette ribbons in a little olive oil.

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium heat. Add the onion and cook, stirring, for 5-6 minutes, or until softened. Add the balsamic vinegar, water and brown sugar and stir to combine. Cook for a further 3-5 minutes or until dark and sticky. Season with salt and pepper.

Place the pizza bases on the wire racks, rough-side down, and use the back of a spoon to spread evenly with the pizza sauce.

Sprinkle over the dried oregano (see ingredients list) and top evenly with the caramelised onions, courgette ribbons and goat cheese

Bake the pizzas on the rack for 10 minutes, or until the base is crisp.  TIP:  Placing the pizzas directly on the wire rack helps the base to crisp up.

Season the pizzas with a good grind of black pepper and slice. Top with the rocket leaves and drizzle with olive oil if you like.